<subSubSection id="40F16514FF9AFFD2FF4AFC215B5AA64D" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9AFFD2FF4AFC215BCAA78D" blockId="4.[151,1127,995,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FF4AFC215856A0CD" bold="true" box="[151,268,995,1019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Very small (3.0- 
<quantity id="CF139B7AFF9AFFD2FE62FC215B4CA0CD" box="[447,534,995,1019]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.7 mm</quantity>
), suboval, black-bronze species (
<figureCitation id="90D02A1AFF9AFFD2FCA5FC215AE0A0CD" box="[888,954,995,1019]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[151,190,1282,1301]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,221,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[151,1126,219,1262]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus. 1 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype (J, 4.0 mm, Negros); 2 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, lectotype (J, 5.0 mm, Luzon); 3 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, holotype (♀, 3.5 mm, Mindanao); 4 – A. (H.) boettcheri (J, 3.9 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 5 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♀, 4.7 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 6 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis (J, 3.5 mm, Mindoro)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331369/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); elytra suboval with small, blue-green postscutellar stripe, frons very slightly convex, lateroposterior pronotal depressions very often with golden green tinge; parameres strongly constricted at apical third, median lobe sharply pointed (
<figureCitation id="90D02A1AFF9AFFD2FE08FB815B79A76D" box="[469,547,1091,1115]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[113,152,1427,1446]" captionTargetBox="[113,1086,219,1277]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[113,1088,219,1278]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 7–14. 7–9 – Habitus. 7 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) palawanensis sp. nov., holotype (J, 3.6 mm, Palawan); 8 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., holotype (J, 3.6 mm, Sibuyan); 9 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., allotype (♀, 3.9 mm, Luzon). 10–14 – Aedeagi (not in the scale). 10 – A. (H.) palawanensis sp. nov., holotype; 11 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, Mindoro; 12 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., holotype; 13 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, Luzon, Abra province; 14 – A. (H.) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype, Negros." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Sexual dimorphism nearly absent: the female differs from the male only by somewhat stouter body and by nearly parallel anterior two thirds of elytra which nearly completely cover the abdomen (elytra of male more sphenoidal, not completely covering abdomen) – see 
<figureCitation id="90D02A1AFF9AFFD2FDFBFB615BD6A78D" box="[550,652,1187,1211]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[151,190,1282,1301]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,221,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[151,1126,219,1262]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus. 1 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype (J, 4.0 mm, Negros); 2 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, lectotype (J, 5.0 mm, Luzon); 3 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, holotype (♀, 3.5 mm, Mindanao); 4 – A. (H.) boettcheri (J, 3.9 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 5 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♀, 4.7 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 6 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis (J, 3.5 mm, Mindoro)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331369/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Figs. 3, 6</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9AFFD2FF4AFB015B5AA64D" blockId="4.[151,1127,995,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FF4AFB0158C8A7ED" bold="true" box="[151,402,1219,1243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9AFFD2FE45FB075A11A7EA" authorityName=": BILY" authorityYear="1990" box="[408,843,1219,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaoensis" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FE45FB0758A2A7EA" box="[408,504,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FDD5FB075BC1A7EA" box="[520,667,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Haplanthaxia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FD76FB075A11A7EA" box="[683,843,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">mindanaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9AFFD2FC0AFB0759B2A7CA" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1900" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weyersi" subGenus="Anthaxia">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FC0AFB075AB4A7EA" box="[983,1006,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FC20FB075D07A7EA" box="[1021,1117,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Anthaxia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FF4AFB2759B2A7CA" box="[151,232,1253,1276]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">weyersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="70FC760FFF9AFFD2FF25FB21583FA7CD" box="[248,357,1251,1275]" name="Indonesia" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="CA2FF87DFF9AFFD2FEADFB215896A7CD" box="[368,460,1251,1275]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="CA2FF87DFF9AFFD2FE0AFB215B52A7CD" box="[471,520,1251,1275]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Java</collectingRegion>
) which differs from 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9AFFD2FD34FB275A81A7CA" authorityName=": BILY" authorityYear="1990" box="[745,987,1251,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaoensis" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FD34FB275A5AA7CA" box="[745,768,1253,1276]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FCCDFB275A71A7CA" box="[784,811,1253,1276]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FCE6FB275A81A7CA" box="[827,987,1253,1276]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">mindanaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only weakly by the characters distinguishing both subgenera (well-expressed only in males), by the elytral epipleura reaching only the apical, rounded part of the elytra, by the lighter colouration, by the more sphenoidal body and by the form of the median lobe, which is slender and more pointed in 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9AFFD2FED4FAA758A3A64A" authorityName=": BILY" authorityYear="1990" box="[265,505,1379,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaoensis" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FED4FAA7587BA64A" box="[265,289,1381,1404]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FEEDFAA75810A64A" box="[304,330,1381,1404]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FE84FAA758A3A64A" box="[345,505,1381,1404]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">mindanaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="40F16514FF9AFFD2FF4AFA41586BA6CD" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9AFFD2FF4AFA41586BA6CD" blockId="4.[151,1127,995,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FF4AFA41585FA6AD" bold="true" box="[151,261,1411,1435]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Remarks.</emphasis>
In the female 
<typeStatus id="D750883DFF9AFFD2FE4AFA4158AEA6AD" box="[407,500,1411,1435]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">holotype</typeStatus>
(see 
<figureCitation id="90D02A1AFF9AFFD2FDF4FA415B3EA6AD" box="[553,612,1411,1435]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[151,190,1282,1301]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,221,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[151,1126,219,1262]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus. 1 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype (J, 4.0 mm, Negros); 2 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, lectotype (J, 5.0 mm, Luzon); 3 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, holotype (♀, 3.5 mm, Mindanao); 4 – A. (H.) boettcheri (J, 3.9 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 5 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♀, 4.7 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 6 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis (J, 3.5 mm, Mindoro)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331369/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) the elytra completely cover the abdomen, which was the main reason for attributing this species to the 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9AFFD2FD3BFA675ADDA68A" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1900" box="[742,903,1443,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weyersi" subGenus="Anthaxia">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FD3BFA675BA4A68A" box="[742,766,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FCD3FA675A7CA68A" box="[782,806,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FCEBFA675ADDA68A" box="[822,903,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">weyersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (
<bibRefCitation id="6C7A4B6EFF9AFFD2FBE8FA61598BA6ED" author="BILY S." pageId="4" pageNumber="437" pagination="128 - 140" refId="ref5568" refString="BILY S. 1990: A revision of Anthaxia (Anthaxia) weyersi, species-group from South-East Asia (Coleoptera, Buprestidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca 87: 128 - 140." type="journal article" year="1990">BÍLÝ 1990</bibRefCitation>
). As a matter of fact, all members of this species-group are very close to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9AFFD2FF4AFA275870A6CA" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,298,1509,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9AFFD2FF4AFA275870A6CA" box="[151,298,1509,1532]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Haplanthaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
